Farticle%2F4a3ba3%2Fcalifornia-dmv-suspends-cruises-self-driving-car-license-after-pedestrian-injury%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eobtained%20by%20Vice%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20California%20Department%20of%20Motor%20Vehicles%20(DMV)%20referred%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcruise-driverless-car-robotaxi-runs-over-woman-san-francisco-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ean%20incident%20from%20earlier%20this%20year%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20a%20pedestrian%20was%20hit%20by%20a%20separate%20vehicle%20and%20fell%20into%20the%20path%20of%20a%20Cruise%20robotaxi%2C%20which%20ran%20them%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20autonomous%20car%20hard-braked%20and%2C%20having%20detected%20a%20collision%2C%20attempted%20to%20pull%20over%2C%20traveling%2020%20feet%20at%20a%20speed%20of%207%20mph%20while%20the%20pedestrian%20was%20still%20underneath%20the%20car.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DMV%20said%20that%20its%20representatives%20met%20with%20Cruise%20the%20following%20day%20and%20were%20shown%20video%20footage%20of%20the%20accident%20captured%20by%20the%20robotaxi's%20cameras.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20they%20said%20that%20the%20self-driving%20company%20did%20not%20disclose%20the%20footage%20of%20the%20car%20attempting%20to%20pull%20over%20immediately%20after%20the%20crash%2C%20and%20only%20provided%20it%20several%20days%20later%20at%20the%20DMV's%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20subsequent%20maneuvering%20of%20the%20vehicle%20indicates%20that%20Cruise's%20vehicles%20may%20lack%20the%20ability%20to%20respond%20in%20a%20safe%20and%20appropriate%20manner%20during%20incidents%20involving%20a%20pedestrian%20so%20as%20not%20to%20unnecessarily%20put%20the%20pedestrian%20or%20others%20at%20risk%20of%20further%20injury%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20DMV%20wrote%2C%20per%20Vice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20Vice%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Cruise%20disputed%20the%20DMV's%20report.%20%26quot%3BI%20can%2