20Such%20fears%20have%20grown%20after%20the%20US%20slapped%20embargoes%20on%20Russia%20and%20Iran%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPredictably%2C%20financial%20markets%20have%20been%20rife%20with%20speculation%20in%20recent%20months%20that%20Beijing%20is%20calculatedly%20cutting%20back%20investments%20in%20US%20bonds%20to%20undermine%20the%20dollar%20and%20dent%20the%20pre-eminence%20of%20Treasuries%20as%20the%20most%20reliable%20asset%20class%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that's%20a%20mere%20myth%2C%20according%20to%20at%20least%20expert.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20China's%20holdings%20of%20Treasuries%20have%20indeed%20fallen%20by%20some%20%24220%20billion%20since%20the%20end%20of%202021%2C%20the%20reality%20is%20more%20nuanced%2C%20according%20to%20strategists%20at%20the%20UK-based%20Lloyds%20Banking%20Group%20led%20by%20Sam%20Hill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20them%2C%20the%20decline%20in%20the%20Asian%20country's%20ownership%20of%20US%20government%20bonds%20also%20indicates%20some%20other%20reasons%20than%20a%20deliberate%20shift%20away%20from%20American%20assets%2C%20such%20as%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBeijing%20has%20diversified%20some%20of%20its%20investments%20into%20so-called%20American%20agency%20debt%20%E2%80%94%20securities%20issued%20by%20government-sponsored%20enterprise%20or%20a%20federal%20agency%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhich%20is%20US%20government%20in%20all%20but%20name.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20shrinkage%20of%20China's%20US%20debt%20holdings%20also%20reflects%20a%20drop%20in%20bond%20valuations%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20raised%20interest%20rates%20at%20the%20fastest%20pace%20in%20four%20decades.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChina%20may%20have%20sold%20US%20Treasuries%20(USTs)%20to%20raise%20dollars%20that%20it%20would%20in%20turn%20sell%20in%20the%20local%20market%20to%20stabilize%20its%20own%20currency%2C%20the%20yuan%2C%20during%20times%20of%20elevated%20exchange-rate%20volatility.%20The%20Chinese%20currency%20plunged%20to%20an%20almost%2016-year%20low%20last%20month%2C%20and%20is%20currently%20on%20track%20for%20the%20biggest%20two-year%20decline%20in%20more%20than%20three%20decades.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOfficial%20data%20%26quot%3Bsuggests%20there's%20been%20a%20persistent%20decline%20in%20Chinese%20US%20bond%20holdings.%20To%20many%20this%20reflects%20a%20conscious%20shift%20by%20China%20to%20reduce%20its%20exposure%20to%20US%20government%20debt%2C%20amid%20a%20period%20of%20increasingly%20strained%20geopolitical%20tension%2C%20accelerated%20by%20the%20seizure%20of%20Russian%20foreign%20assets%20following%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%20Hill%20and%20colleagues%20wrote%20in%20a%20research%20note%20published%20earlier%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20you%20do%20not%20need%20to%20scratch%20deep%20to%20reveal%20it's%20myth%2C%20USTs%20appeal%20still%20looks%20enduring%2C%26quot%3B%20they%C2%A0%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20slide%20in%20China's%20Treasury%20holdings%20attracted%20much%20attention%20particularly%20as%20the%20declines%20accelerated%20over%20the%20past%20year%20and%20a%20half%2C%20a%20time%20when%20US%20bonds%20have%20been%20in%20the%20throes%20of%20a%20historic%20rout.%20The%20selloff%20saw%20benchmark%2010-year%20yields%20more%20than%20triple%20since%20the%20end-2021%20to%20breach%20the%20psychologically%20important%205%25%20mark%20this%20week%2C%20fueled%20by%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20aggressive%20interest-rate%20increases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20longer%20term%2C%20any%20deterioration%20in%20relations%20between%20the%20West%20and%20rival%20countries%20such%20as%20China%20could%20actually%20boost%20demand%20for%20the%20safe-haven%20appeal%20of%20Treasuries%2C%20according%20to%20the%20analysts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20value%20on%20being%20able%20to%20hold%20assets%20(directly%20or%20indirectly)%20in%20democracies%20bound%20by%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%20The%20more%20autocratic%20non-democratic%20re