0India's%20next%20two%20World%20Cup%20matches%20as%20he%20is%20yet%20to%20recover%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report.%20Pandya%20had%20slipped%20in%20his%20follow-through%20while%20playing%20against%20Bangladesh%20in%20Pune%20on%20October%2019%20and%20missed%20the%20clash%20against%20New%20Zealand%20in%20Dharamsala%20on%20October%2022.%20The%20Bardoa%20player%20had%20reported%20to%20National%20Cricket%20Academy%20on%20Monday%20in%20Bengaluru%20for%20injury%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Board%20of%20Control%20for%20Cricket%20in%20India%20(BCCI)%20had%20earlier%20suggested%20that%20Hardik%20would%20travel%20to%20Lucknow%20for%20India's%20next%20match%20against%20England%20but%20that%20no%20longer%20seems%20doable.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHardik%20is%20still%20under%20medication.%20While%20the%20swelling%20on%20his%20left%20ankle%20has%20subsided%20considerably%2C%20he%20will%20start%20bowling%20only%20towards%20the%20weekend.%20Right%20now%2C%20important%20is%20to%20give%20him%20time%20to%20recover%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20NCA%20source%20told%20PTI.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%20India%20are%20in%20a%20very%20strong%20position%20to%20make%20the%20semifinals%2C%20having%20won%20all%20five%20matches%20so%20far%2C%20Pandya%20could%20easily%20be%20rested%20for%20the%20next%20two%20matches%20that%20will%20allow%20him%20complete%20recovery%20before%20the%20knock-outs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPandya%20has%20suffered%20a%20bad%20sprain%20but%20fortunately%20not%20a%20fracture.%20The%20BCCI%20medical%20team%20wants%20to%20take%20maximum%20precaution.%20He%20is%20likely%20to%20miss%20next%20two%20to%20three%20matches.%20The%20team%20wants%20him%20fully%20fit%20for%20the%20knock-out%20stage%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20a%20BCCI%20source.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20next%20play%20against%20defending%20champions%20England%20on%20October%2029%20in%20Lucknow%20and%20take%20on%20Sri%20Lanka%20in%20Mumbai%20on%20November%202.%20Pandya's%20absence%20had%20created%20space%20for%2